        "process": "<div>Add 1/4th Teaspoon each of salt and turmeric powder to the prawns, mix well and keep aside for 10 minutes<\/div><div>Do the same with potatoes.<\/div><div>In a small bowl add all of the spice powder, ginger garlic paste along with 3 Tablespoons of water. Mix well, keep aside.<\/div><div>Heat 1 Tablespoon of oil in a pan.<\/div><div>Add the prawns and fry on high heat for just a minute.<\/div><div>Then take them out and add another Tablespoon of oil in the same pan.<\/div><div>Fry the potatoes in that oil for 2-3 minutes, then take them out.<\/div><div>Now heat the remaining oil.<\/div><div>Saute bay leaf and cumin seeds for few seconds.<\/div><div>Then add the spice mixture and cook for 2 minutes on low flame.<\/div><div>Then add grated tomato along with some salt and cook until oil separates.<\/div><div>Add the fried potatoes, mix well for 2 minutes.<\/div><div>Then add hot water, cover the pan and cook until the potatoes become 80% soft.<\/div><div>Next add the fried prawns and green chilies, mix well and cook for 2-3 minutes on low flame.<\/div><div>When the gravy becomes thick add ghee, mix well and turn off the heat.<\/div>",
