        "process": "<div>Marinate the fish fillets with some salt, half Tablespoon of black pepper powder, 1 Tablespoon of ginger and garlic paste and lemon juice for 1 hour.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-cf868c7b-55a5-48da-af06-043302cf4870.jpg\" /><div>In the meantime, heat 2 Tablespoons of white oil in a pan.<\/div><div>Add chopped onion. Cook till golden in color.<\/div><div>Then add the remaining ginger - garlic paste and chopped green chilies. Cook for 3 minutes.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-38241d78-7fcc-4ded-8d24-852f92b6da9a.jpg\" /><div>Add salt, a big pinch of sugar, soy sauce and tomato ketchup. Mix well.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-d66a5dce-8224-48c6-a862-5b1565e53025.jpg\" /><div>Then add the white fish cubes. Cook for 10 minutes.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-c2c2b70f-04d6-4efe-88c5-fe5356dafe3d.jpg\" /><div>Add red chilli powder, remaining black pepper powder and red chilli powder. Mix and cook for another 10 minutes.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-b704193d-6997-4e45-97fc-bf2c09c7ffc8.jpg\" /><div>With the help of your spatula make the fish crumbly.<\/div><div>Lastly add 2 - 3 Tablespoons of breadcrumbs to the fish mixture. Cook for 4 minutes and turn off the heat.<\/div><div>Breadcrumbs will absorb all the moisture from the mixture, so that you can easily roll the fillets.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-2f71250c-aec3-4b9a-88d1-84cd86b3117c.jpg\" /><div>Let the mixture come to room temperature.<\/div><div>Then take some portion and make flatten ball.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-3d0962a1-4057-4b80-930f-245f0160316b.jpg\" /><div>Place the flatten mixture on the edge of a marinated fish fillet.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-19d103c9-1de8-4bdd-a9ad-d019bbbbb001.jpg\" /><div>Now roll the fillet tightly with the stuffing.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-f2ea7cbd-bebd-42e2-b986-2b32a7a5d1d9.jpg\" /><div>Very lightly coat the rolls in the breadcrumbs first.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-0bc1dc60-382c-468b-87c1-165ee438585a.jpg\" /><div>Then beat the egg with cornflour, pinch of salt and black pepper powder very well.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-3eac2e34-8f56-4e84-90cc-6d1c9f533e13.jpg\" /><div>Take lightly coated roll, dip into the egg mixture and again roll in the breadcrumbs.<\/div><div>With gentle pressure of your hand seal the edges of the roll properly.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-b18262c7-b100-47c2-a5d5-b67a32132339.jpg\" /><div>Keep them in fridge for 30 minutes.<\/div><div>Then fry them in hot oil for 10 - 12 minutes.<\/div><img src=\"recipeimages/fish-roll-53827377-f5cb-4f12-be04-c0c93e5e44d6.jpg\"  style='width:45%'/>",
