        "shortDesc": "Every place in this world has their own tea stalls and also some unique dishes. You can never match the taste of tea stall's food with big restaurant's food ... a huge difference !  One of the famous item of those stalls in India is 'toast'. You can get so many types of toast from them like 'butter toast', 'french toast', 'plain toast' etc. I love to eat 'dim pauruti' or in fancy words 'savory french toast' as snack with some ketchup. I used to take these toasts in my lunch box also. They are delicious and very easy to make. Try this in your kitchen and enjoy.",
