        "end-pic": "recipeimages/chicken-keema-paratha-end.jpg",
        "shortDesc": "Don't know about you, but I love 'keema' / mince form of meat. I have already posted so many recipes on 'keema' and this time I made paratha with mince chicken. The authentic recipe calls for 'mutton keema' but didn't have it that time, so made it with chicken and the parathas came out perfectly fine. These breads can be enjoyed with pickle, raita or any type of gravy. The recipe is very simple but you need to mince the chicken very fine like paste, otherwise paratha will not come out perfect. Try this recipe in your kitchen and let me know how it turned out.",
        "add-title": "Stuffed Flat bread with minced Chicken",
